{"lemma":"فَتْحُ","slug":"فَتْحُ","root":"ف.ت.ح","root_slug":"ف-ت-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَتْح","root":"فتح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":12},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32873","n32874","n32878","n32879"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%92%D8%AD%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to open (“to make something accessible”)","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"يَسْمَحُ مِقْلَادٌ بِمُرُورِ التَّيَّارِ الْكَهْرَبَائِيِّ عِنْدَ إِغْلَاقِهِ وَيَمْنَعُ الْمُرُورَ عِنْدَ فَتْحِهِ","english":"A switch allows the passage of electric current when it is turned on and prevents its passage when it is turned off."},{"text":"فَتَحَ زَكِي عَيْنَيْهِ","english":"Zaki opened his eyes."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to conquer, occupy, take possession of"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to disclose to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to explain, expound"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prompt"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to assist"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to begin"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to decide","examples":[{"text":"فَتَحَ الْفَأْل","english":"to take as an omen"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mark (a consonant) with a fatha"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to offer (a price)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to broach (a subject)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to open in large numbers or thoroughly","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ ٱلَّذِينَ كَذَّبُوا بِآيَاتِنَا وَٱسْتَكْبَرُوا عَنْهَا لَا تُفَتَّحُ لَهُمْ أَبْوَابُ ٱلسَّمَاءِ وَلَا يَدْخُلُونَ ٱلْجَنَّةَ حَتَّى يَلِجَ ٱلْجَمَلُ فِي سَمِّ ٱلْخِيَاطِ","english":"Indeed, those who deny Our signs and disdain them—the gates of the heaven will not be opened for them, nor shall they enter paradise until the camel passes through the needle's eye"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَتَحَ (fataḥa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opening"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"disclosure, overture, beginning"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conquest, victory, an outcome; occupation of a fortified place, opening of an enemy's defenses"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"help"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the vowel sign fatha"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Fatah (a major Palestinian political party and the largest faction of the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO))"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *pataḥ-.\n\nCognate with Akkadian 𒁉𒌈 (pītum) and Biblical Hebrew פֶּתַח (pɛ́ṯaḥ)."},"ipa":["/fa.ta.ħa/","/fat.ta.ħa/","/fatħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32873","headword_ar":"فَتَحَ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, MA, Msb, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatoHN","text_ar":"فَتْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraja","text_ar":"فَرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he unlocked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agolaqa","text_ar":"اَغْلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) a door; (S, A, MA, Msb;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft~H","text_ar":"فتّح","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfttH","text_ar":"افتتح","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fat~aHotu","text_ar":"فَتَّحْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abowaAba","text_ar":"الاَبْوَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I opened the doors"},{"kind":"text","text":"], this verb being with teshdeed to denote multiplicity [of the objects]; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstftH","text_ar":"استفتح","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfttH","text_ar":"افتتح","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * K;) i. e. each of these signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he opened"},{"kind":"text","text":"a door; (TK;) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotafotaHotu","text_ar":"اِسْتَفْتَحْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotataHotuhu","text_ar":"اِفْتَتَحْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I opened the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the former signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demanded, the opening of the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAba","text_ar":"البَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a yasotafotiHu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ يَسْتَفْتِحُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came opening the door;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demanding, the opening of the door;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the latter being the more obvious meaning]. (A, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2328},{"kind":"text","text":"[Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA yufotaHu AlEayonu EalaY mivolihi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا يُفْتَحُ العَيْنُ عَلَى مِثْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one, the eye will not be opened upon the like of him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHotu AlqanaApa","text_ar":"فَتَحْتُ القَنَاةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I opened the conduit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in order that the water might run, and irrigate the seed-produce. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa bayona rijolayohi","text_ar":"فَتَحَ بَيْنَ رِجْلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made an opening between his legs; he parted his legs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraja bayonahumaA","text_ar":"فَرَجَ بَيْنَهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rhw","text_ar":"رهو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa A^aSaAbiEa","text_ar":"فَتَحَ اَصَابِعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijolayohi","text_ar":"رِجْلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He parted his toes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"if not a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataxa","text_ar":"فَتَخَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it seems probably to be from the fact of its being expl. as meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he inclined the ends of his toes towards the back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the upper part, of his foot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHato","text_ar":"فَتَحَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a she-camel, [and of a sheep or goat (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatuwHN","text_ar":"فَتُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She had wide orifices to her teats;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AftHt","text_ar":"افتحت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfttHt","text_ar":"افتتحت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TK: but this I do not find in the K.) ―         -b7-  [The following meanings are tropical.] ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa","text_ar":"فَتَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatoHN","text_ar":"فَتْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfttH","text_ar":"افتتح","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He laid open by invasion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"to ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":") such a person, or such a people, (see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TarafN","text_ar":"طَرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he conquered, won,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took by force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) a country (A, Msb, K, TA) of the unbelievers, (A, TA,) or of a people with whom there was war. (K, TA.) ―         -b9-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHahu","text_ar":"فَتَحَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He granted it, permitted it, allowed it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it to be unrestricted, to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"See Ksh and Bd in xxxv. 2.] ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa Almu$okila","text_ar":"فَتَحَ المُشْكِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He explained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made clear, that which was dubious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confused."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in vii. 87.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaHo sir~aka EalaY~a laA","text_ar":"اِفْتَحْ سِرَّكَ عَلَىَّ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"عَلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Open,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reveal, thy secret to me; not to such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b11-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa","text_ar":"فَتَحَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He taught him, informed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquainted him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa Ealayohi bika*aA","text_ar":"فَتَحَ عَلَيْهِ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He taught him such a thing, informed him of it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquainted him with it."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b12-  And hence, (TA,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prompted him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he recited to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, an Imám, A, Msb, or a reciter, A, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what he was unable to utter"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of forgetfulness"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that he might know it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa EalaY mani A@sotaqoraA^ahu","text_ar":"فَتَحَ عَلَى مَنِ ا@سْتَقْرَاَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He recited"},{"kind":"text","text":"something"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him who desired him to do so, the latter being unable to do it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b13-  And, said of God, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided him against his enemy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made him to be victorious, to conquer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to overcome;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSarahu","text_ar":"نَصَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Msb.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futiHa EalaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُتِحَ عَلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one became fortunate; possessed of good fortune; favoured by the world,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by worldly circumstances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa A@ll~`hu Ealayohimo futuwHFA","text_ar":"فَتَحَ ا@للّٰهُ عَلَيْهِمْ فُتُوحًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyrapF","text_ar":"كَثِيرَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  is said of persons who have been rained upon [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God bestowed upon them many,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant, first rains"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa bayonahumo","text_ar":"فَتَحَ بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"بَيْنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona AlxaSomayoni","text_ar":"بَيْنَ الخَصْمَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatoHN","text_ar":"فَتْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futaAHapN","text_ar":"فُتَاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitaAHapN","text_ar":"فِتَاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are syn. therewith [app. as inf. ns.], (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwHapN","text_ar":"فُتُوحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitaAHN","text_ar":"فِتَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) in the dial. of Himyer, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He judged"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two litigants."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaHo bayonanaA","text_ar":"اِفْتَحْ بَيْنَنَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Judge thou between us:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) thus in the Kur vii. 87. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aHosana fitaAHatahu","text_ar":"مَا اَحْسَنَ فِتَاحَتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How good is his judging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judgment !"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b17-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa AlHarofa","text_ar":"فَتَحَ الحَرْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a conventional phrase in grammar and lexicology,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pronounced the letter with the vowel-sound termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatoH","text_ar":"فَتْح"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he marked the letter with the sign of that vowel-sound."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","MA","A","TA","T","L","S"]},{"entry_id":"n32874","headword_ar":"فتّح","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, first sentence, in two places. ―         -b2-  [Also, said of a medicine &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It opened"},{"kind":"text","text":"the bowels;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acted as an aperient:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it removed"},{"kind":"text","text":"obstructions: see the act. part. n.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n32878","headword_ar":"فَتْحٌ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataHa","text_ar":"فَتَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Msb, &c.) ―         -b2-  [As a subst.,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Conquest"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a country: (K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwHN","text_ar":"فُتُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) [and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwHaAtN","text_ar":"فُتُوحَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN AlfatoHi","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ الفَتْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means particularly (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of the conquest of Mekkeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of resurrection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mujáhid, L.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aid against an enemy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"victory;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorN","text_ar":"نَصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataAHapN","text_ar":"فَتَاحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Means of subsistence, with which God gives aid:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first of the rain called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwasomiY~","text_ar":"الوَسْمِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatuwHN","text_ar":"فَتُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see again in what follows]: (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first of any rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futoHapN","text_ar":"فُتْحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwHN","text_ar":"فُتُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatuwHN","text_ar":"فَتُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) [see the mention of this voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoHN","text_ar":"فَيْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] but MF strongly reprobates this latter form, and observes that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a pl. measure is absolutely unknown. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbati AlA^aroDu futuwHN","text_ar":"اَصَابَتِ الاَرْضُ فُتُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"First rains fell upon the land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water running"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a spring or other source:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water running upon the surface of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water for which a channel is opened to a tract of land for its irrigation thereby:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a river,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rivulet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canal of running water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA suqiYa biAlfatoHi fafiyhi","text_ar":"مَا سُقِىَ بِالفَتْحِ فَفِيهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu$oru","text_ar":"العُشْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA suqiYa fatoHFA","text_ar":"مَا سُقِىَ فَتْحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatoHFA","text_ar":"فَتْحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here in the accus. case as an inf. n., i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA futiHa A_ilayohi maA='u","text_ar":"مَا فُتِحَ اـِلَيْهِ مَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anohaAri fatoHFA","text_ar":"الاَنْهَارِ فَتْحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, L, *) occurring in a trad., means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the case of that"},{"kind":"text","text":"(relating to the several sorts of seed-produce, and palm-trees,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2329},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irrigated by means of the channel opened to conduct to it the water of the river"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rivers"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tithe"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of the produce shall be taken]. (L.) ―         -b7-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of insertion of the tang of the iron head that enters into the shaft"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an arrow: (K, * TA:) pl. as above. (TA.) ―         -b8-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naboE","text_ar":"نَبْع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~ap xaDoraA='","text_ar":"حَبَّة خَضْرَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the pistachia terebinthus"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except that it is red, sweet, and round; eaten by men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  [As a conventional term in grammar and lexicology,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain vowel-sound, well-known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatoHapN","text_ar":"فَتْحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sign of that vowel-sound."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","L","A","S","AHn"]},{"entry_id":"n32879","headword_ar":"فُتُحٌ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEulN","text_ar":"فُعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbN futuHN","text_ar":"بَابٌ فُتُحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide, open, door:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large, wide, door."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAruwrapN futuHN","text_ar":"قَارُورَةٌ فُتُحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide-headed bottle"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flash:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bottle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flash, having neither a stopper nor a case:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, Msb, K:) because, if so, it is open. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Ks","Msb"]}]}}